<br>
I play poker, I play a LOT of poker.<br>
<br>
In poker you have nice players, mean players, good players, bad players, drunk players, etc etc...  In poker, the object is always to win, to take the other guy's money.  I like to equate this to what PvP is all about.  You can be as nice and gentile as you want, but the goal is to take the other guy's money, or, to kill him for exp loss and insigs.  The more the other guy loses, the more you win.  Pino just got his whole bankroll wiped out.  It happens.<br>
<br>
The nature of this game is to hurt the other guy.  Deal with it.  Nice poker players typically lose.<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts.<br>
